snippet.textDisplay: I like Dax as a rapper but I gotta be honest that the yelling raps are really out of place with the vibe of the song. Also, this is essentially the 3rd & 4th verses for Dear God and like that song, he reveals just how naive his concept of heaven, hell and God actually are. It's like, entry level spirituality propped up as something profound when it's quite commonplace. Again, I like Dax as a rapper, especially when he's calm and clear...not hating on him. This just lacked depth to me and the analogies are antiquated. Live being evil spelled backwards? That's a very well known analogy. And that was the most relevant line. 3 stars for me.

snippet.textDisplay: As a Christian, I do have many questions myself. There are certain things I don’t understand as well. But I do know that the terrible things of this world are not caused by God. We as people and followers of Christ have failed to teach and stand up for what’s right. Ever since I accepted Christ I began to realize that none of this is God’s fault. It’s not wrong to question God, but those who point the finger at Him are fools. The Bible says that Satan comes to steal, kill, and destroy. It also says that Satan is the god of this world. But that’s not God’s fault. God gave us free will! He also blessed us the gift of love! 1 Corinthians 13:4-8 describes what real, true love is.... also, remember that God created YOU. God is holy and righteous and requires us to obey His commands in order to enter the gates of heaven. Even one little tiny white lie is enough to send us to eternal damnation.. The BAD NEWS is that you and I have broken most (if not all) of these commandments.. the GOOD NEWS is that, 2000 years ago, He sent His one and only son, Jesus Christ, to die for each and every one of our sins... In order to be saved, all we have to do is repent (which means to confess and ask for forgiveness of our sins)  and accept Him as our Lord and savior.... of course when I accepted Christ as my savior, I did have many many questions and misconceptions. That’s why there’s a Bible and that’s why we can pray to Him. As a Christian, I do also want to point out that I am not perfect and I’m not better than everyone else. I am human just each and every one of you. The only difference is that I know that I am saved and I’m reaching out to each and every one of you to tell you that you are so very loved by such a perfect God. I know I can’t answer all the other questions that people may have, but I do encourage y’all to try researching through scripture or by asking other well educated Christians... God is coming soon! I pray that this reaches someone who is lost so that they may be found. ♥️ God bless.
